# .cursorrules — FotoHaven
# Fallback context file for Cursor and other agents that read .cursorrules.
# Primary context is in CLAUDE.md — read that first.

You are working on FotoHaven, a Next.js 14 photo handoff platform for event photographers.
The primary deployment is an old Android phone running Termux + PM2 + Cloudflare Tunnel.

## Critical rules — never violate these

1. Read CLAUDE.md before writing any code. It has the full spec.
2. Read AGENTS.md before implementing any roadmap feature. It has task specs.
3. All storage I/O goes through src/lib/storage.ts — never import AWS SDK directly.
4. All DB access goes through src/lib/db.ts — never `new PrismaClient()`.
5. Colours are CSS variables from globals.css — never hardcode hex values.
6. TypeScript strict mode — no `any`, no `@ts-ignore`.
7. Do not run `prisma migrate` — use `prisma db push` only (SQLite MVP mode).
8. Do not add packages without user confirmation.

## Stack
Next.js 14.1.4 · React 18 · Prisma 5.11 · SQLite · Cloudflare R2 · Tailwind (minimal)

## Key paths
- Data models: prisma/schema.prisma
- Storage layer: src/lib/storage.ts
- DB client: src/lib/db.ts
- Types: src/types/index.ts
- Design system: src/app/globals.css
- API routes: src/app/api/**/route.ts
- Pages: src/app/**/page.tsx
